(148, 4, 'http://feeds.washingtonpost.com/c/34656/f/636708/s/2fdc9e03/sc/4/l/0L0Swashingtonpost0N0Cblogs0Cblogpost0Cpost0C40A0Emaps0Ethat0Eexplain0Ethe0Eworld0C20A130C0A80C120C5775d2140E0A3640E11e30Ebfc50E40A6b92860A3b20Iblog0Bhtml0Dwprss0Frss0Iworld/story01.htm', '2013-08-12 19:32:13', '40 maps that explain the world', 'maps,that,explain,world', 'Maps can be a remarkably powerful tool for understanding the world and how it works, but they show only what you ask them to. So when we saw a post sweeping the Web titled &quot;40 maps they didn&#039;t teach you in school,&quot; one of which happens to be a WorldViews original, I thought we might be able to contribute our own collection. Some of these are pretty nerdy, but I think they&#039;re no less fascinating and easily understandable. A majority are original to this blog, with others from a variety of sources. I&#039;ve included a link for further reading on close to every one. Read full article &amp;#62;&amp;#62;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;', 'maps,remarkably,powerful,tool,understanding,world,works,they,show,only,what,them,when,post,sweeping,titled,didn,teach,school,which,happens,worldviews,original,thought,might,able,contribute,collection,some,these,pretty,nerdy,think,less,fascinating,easily,understandable,majority,this,blog,with,others,from,variety,sources,included,link,further,reading,close,every,read,full,article,nbsp', '', 'maps,that,explain,world,remarkably,powerful,tool,understanding,works,they,show,only,what,them,when,post,sweeping,titled,didn,teach,school,which,happens,worldviews,original,thought,might,able,contribute,collection,some,these,pretty,nerdy,think,less,fascinating,easily,understandable,majority,this,blog,with,others,from,variety,sources,included,link,further,reading,close,every,read,full,article,nbsp', NULL, '2013-08-13 03:39:46'),
